    <h1>Digital Signatures</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Wikipedia (CC BY-SA 4.0) · <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signature"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Digital signature</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>digital signature</strong> proves that a message came from the holder of a private key, and that it was not altered in transit. Anyone with the corresponding public key can verify it. Signatures enable trust without trusted third parties.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Sign and verify flow -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 200" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
